                  a: 'PMF (Probability Mass Function) gives P(X=x) directly for discrete RVs — values are probabilities in [0,1] summing to 1. PDF (Probability Density Function) for continuous RVs gives probability per unit length — it is a density, not a probability. P(a≤X≤b) = ∫ₐᵇ f(x)dx. Since f(x) is a density, it can exceed 1 as long as the integral over all x equals 1. For example, a Uniform(0, 0.5) has f(x)=2 everywhere in [0,0.5], but ∫₀^0.5 2dx = 1. In code: scipy.stats.norm.pdf(0) = 0.3989, but scipy.stats.uniform(scale=0.5).pdf(0.25) = 2.0.',
