1st moment — Mean: μ = E[X] = Σxᵢ/n
2nd moment — Variance: σ² = E[(X−μ)²] = E[X²] − μ²
3rd moment — Skewness: γ₁ = E[(X−μ)³] / σ³
  > 0: right tail longer (mass pulled right)
  < 0: left tail longer (mass pulled left)
  = 0: symmetric

4th moment — Kurtosis: γ₂ = E[(X−μ)⁴] / σ⁴ − 3  (excess kurtosis)
  = 0: Normal distribution (mesokurtic)
  > 0: heavier tails than Normal (leptokurtic) — e.g. financial returns, attention weights
  < 0: lighter tails than Normal (platykurtic) — e.g. Uniform distribution

Important: Var(X+Y) = Var(X) + Var(Y) + 2·Cov(X,Y)
For independent X,Y: Var(X+Y) = Var(X) + Var(Y)  — variances add`,
