              overview: `MLE finds θ that makes the observed data most probable.

Likelihood (iid observations):
  L(θ; x₁,...,xₙ) = ∏ᵢ P(xᵢ | θ)

Log-likelihood (preferred — avoids numerical underflow, turns product → sum):
  ℓ(θ) = Σᵢ log P(xᵢ | θ)

θ̂_MLE = argmax_θ ℓ(θ)

